cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.IR, cs.SE. 

The paper addresses the problem of storing and retrieving multiple versions of documents or records in a distributed environment, which is a common problem in data storage and retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the design space and trade-offs for building such a system, which falls under the category of cs.DB (Databases). The retrieval queries mentioned in the paper, such as retrieving full or partial versions and evolution histories, suggest that the paper may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The proposed system architecture and tuning knobs indicate that the paper may also fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the use of off-line and online algorithms for storage layout and version handling suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
